# key2 history: threshold_binarize.v (plain B/W) -> barcode_decoder.v
# (Code 39) -> ean13_decoder.v (current). Real testing showed retail
# packaging is EAN-13/UPC-A, not Code 39, so barcode_decoder.v got the
# same treatment threshold_binarize.v got before it: kept in the repo,
# not part of this build. Uncomment + swap into camera_display_top.v's
# key2 mux if Code 39 (asset tags etc) or plain B/W is ever wanted again.
# set_global_assignment -name VERILOG_FILE barcode_decoder.v
# set_global_assignment -name VERILOG_FILE threshold_binarize.v

# Camera -> BNN -> LG3661BH pipeline: roi_binarize_28x28.v crops+downsamples
# a fixed 224x224 center ROI of the live 480x272 frame into the 28x28
# binary image bnn_core.v expects, one frame at a time; seg7_decoder.v
# turns bnn_core.v's digit_out into a 7-segment pattern for the LG3661BH
# (common anode, active-low -- confirmed by user). Both instantiated in
# camera_display_top.v as an always-on background classifier, independent
# of the key1/2/3 display-mode mux. See CLAUDE.md for the ROI math and the
# 8x8-block-OR downsample rationale.
set_global_assignment -name VERILOG_FILE roi_binarize_28x28.v
set_global_assignment -name VERILOG_FILE seg7_decoder.v

# camera_display_top.v's seg7[6:0]/seg7_dp ports (LG3661BH segments a-g +
# decimal point) have NO location assignment yet -- physical wiring to the
# display hasn\'t been confirmed (asked the user which FPGA pins the 8
# wires go to; the answer received back, "LG2661BH", didn\'t actually give
# pin numbers, so this is still open). Compiling as-is will still succeed
# -- Quartus will auto-assign these 8 pins to whatever's free -- but won't
# light up the real display correctly until the location assignments below
# are filled in to match how it's actually wired. Uncomment and fill in
# once known:
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7[0]   # a
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7[1]   # b
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7[2]   # c
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7[3]   # d
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7[4]   # e
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7[5]   # f
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7[6]   # g
# set_location_assignment PIN_xx -to seg7_dp
# set_instance_assignment -name IO_STANDARD "3.3-V LVTTL" -to seg7[0]
